						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1360 (1439 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>In Sanskrit written in Grantha characters. States that <hi rend="bold">Chakrarāya</hi> installed the Daśāvatāra images (in a temple) on the southern bank of the Kāvērī (Śahyajā) at Śrīraṅgam. The details of the date viz., <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1360 in chronogram</hi> (<hi rend="italic">nītiślāghyā</hi>), <hi rend="bold">Kāḷayukti, Mīna, Paurṇamī, Sunday</hi> correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1439, March 1, Sunday.</hi></p>						

